# Architecture Rules

- All `chrome.storage` access must go through `src/lib/storage/` — never call `chrome.storage` directly in UI or background.
- All `chrome.tabs` and `chrome.tabGroups` access must go through `src/lib/tabs/` — never in UI components.
- Svelte components (`.svelte` files) must never call `chrome.*` directly. Use `chrome.runtime.sendMessage` to delegate to background, or call lib functions.
- Storage keys must always use the `tabglider:` prefix.
- The `isSwitching` guard must wrap all autosave handlers in `background/index.ts`. When `isSwitchingRef.value === true`, return early from every autosave code path.
- Profile IDs are slugified names (lowercase, hyphens). Never use Chrome's numeric tab/group IDs as persistent identifiers.
- Internal group refs are UUIDs (`crypto.randomUUID()`). Map between UUID refs and Chrome numeric IDs only within a single switching operation.
